
Date Class

1. What is java.util.Date?
-->java.util.Date is a class used to represent date and time.
    It stores:
    Date
    Time
    Milliseconds since January 1, 1970 (Epoch time)
    
    Package
    
    import java.util.Date;
    
    Example
    
    import java.util.Date;
    
    public class Demo {
    
        public static void main(String[] args) {
    
            Date date = new Date();
    
            System.out.println(date);
        }
    }

Output :
    Tue Jul 22 10:45:20 IST 2026

Interview Points :
      Represents date and time.
      Legacy class.
      Stores milliseconds from Epoch.





2. How to get the current date and time?
-->Using Date
      import java.util.Date;
      
      public class Demo {
      
          public static void main(String[] args) {
      
              Date current = new Date();
      
              System.out.println(current);
          }
      }
Using LocalDate :
      import java.time.LocalDate;
      
      public class Demo {
      
          public static void main(String[] args) {
      
              LocalDate date = LocalDate.now();
      
              System.out.println(date);
          }
      }
Using LocalTime :
      import java.time.LocalTime;
      
      public class Demo {
      
          public static void main(String[] args) {
      
